history.content: If you mean can you try enrolling in class B again without priority, then yes that's fine. If you mean somehow enrolling in class A without losing your spot in class B, that won't be possible.

Hi, 

If I place a delayed swap request for class A to replace class B, would it be possible to re-enroll into class B after I get into class A? 

Thank you, and I’m sorry if this question has already been asked. I looked through all of the recent posts with the word “swap” on them, but I couldn’t find this exact information.
history.subject: Enrolling in a class after swap fulfilled
